<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="404" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[113,700,1541,2004]" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">
Assemelham-se a grandes pentatomídeos, dos quais se distinguem pela cabeça muito pequena, antenas geralmente com quatro artículos, rostro curto, raramente ultrapassando as coxas anteriores e pronoto estendendo-se sobre a base do escutelo. 
<bibRefCitation author="ROLSTON, L. H. &amp; R. L. AALBU &amp; M. J MURRAY &amp; D. A. RIDER" box="[221,444,1687,1710]" journalOrPublisher="Papua New Guinea J. Agric. Forest. Fish." pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="36 - 108" part="36" refId="ref4066" refString="ROLSTON, L. H., R. L. AALBU, M. J MURRAY &amp; D. A. RIDER. 1993. A catalogue of the Tessaratomidae of the world. Papua New Guinea J. Agric. Forest. Fish. 36 (2): 36 - 108." title="A catalogue of the Tessaratomidae of the world" type="journal article" year="1993">
Rolston 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[307,368,1687,1710]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">et al.</emphasis>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
sumarizaram a classifi- cação corrente para a família. Conforme mencionado acima, 
<bibRefCitation author="GAPUD, V. P." box="[196,342,1745,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="865 - 961" refId="ref3072" refString="GAPUD, V. P. 1991. A generic revision of the subfamily Asopinae, with consideration of its phylogenetic position in the family Pentatomidae and superfamily Pentatomoidea (Hemiptera-Heteroptera). Parts. I and II. Philipp. Entomol. 8 (3): 865 - 961." type="journal article" year="1991">Gapud (1991)</bibRefCitation>
e 
<bibRefCitation author="GRAZIA, J. &amp; C. F. SCHWERTNER" box="[374,592,1745,1769]" editor="Claps, L. E. &amp; G. Debandi &amp; S. Roig-Junent" journalOrPublisher="Tucuman, Sociedad Entomologica Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="223 - 234" refId="ref3164" refString="GRAZIA, J. &amp; C. F. SCHWERTNER. 2008. Pentatomidae e Cyrtocoridae. In: Claps, L. E., G. Debandi &amp; S. Roig-Junent (dirs.), Biodiversidad de artropodos argentinos. V. 2. Tucuman, Sociedad Entomologica Argentina. pp. 223 - 234." title="Pentatomidae e Cyrtocoridae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Biodiversidad de artropodos argentinos. V. 2." year="2008">
Grazia 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[453,515,1746,1769]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
discutem as relações de parentesco entre as famílias Tessaratomidade e 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1867" box="[223,352,1805,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Dinidoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dinidoridae</taxonomicName>
. Aclassificação infrafamiliar foi discutida recentemente por 
<bibRefCitation author="KMENT, P. &amp; J. VILIMOVA" box="[421,696,1833,1857]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="1 - 59" part="2363" refId="ref3486" refString="KMENT, P. &amp; J. VILIMOVA. 2010. Thoracic scent efferent system of the Tessaratomidae sensu lato (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Pentatomoidea) with implication to the phylogeny of the family. Zootaxa 2363: 1 - 59." title="Thoracic scent efferent system of the Tessaratomidae sensu lato (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Pentatomoidea) with implication to the phylogeny of the family" type="journal article" year="2010">Kment &amp; Vilimová (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. São conhecidos 45 gêneros e cerca de 235 espécies, com distribuição exclusiva no hemisfério sul, predominantemente nos trópicos do Velho Mundo. Inclui três subfamílias: Tessaratominae, Natalicolinae e Oncome- rinae. Na região Neotropical, apenas o gênero cosmo-
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[737,1324,189,328]" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">
polita 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[810,957,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tessaratomidae" genus="Piezosternum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,957,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">Piezosternum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
está representado, com três espécies. Chave para as espécies neotropicais em 
<bibRefCitation author="PIRAN, A. A." journalOrPublisher="Acta Zool. Lilloana" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="197 - 208" part="26" refId="ref4037" refString="PIRAN, A. A. 1971. La familia Tessaratomidae (Hemiptera-Heteroptera) en la region neotropical. Acta Zool. Lilloana 26: 197 - 208." title="La familia Tessaratomidae (Hemiptera-Heteroptera) en la region neotropical" type="journal article" year="1971">Pirán (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, das quais uma tem registro para a Argentina: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[737,1001,277,300]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[737,884,277,300]" class="Insecta" family="Tessaratomidae" genus="Piezosternum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Piezosternum</taxonomicName>
thunbergi
</emphasis>
, nas províncias de Formosa, Misiones e Corrientes (
<bibRefCitation author="PIRAN, A. A." box="[979,1107,305,328]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zool. Lilloana" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="5 - 10" part="18" refId="ref4007" refString="PIRAN, A. A. 1962. Hemiptera neotropica V. Notas sobre sistematica y zoogeografia de Pentatomidae. Acta Zool. Lilloana 18: 5 - 10." title="Hemiptera neotropica V. Notas sobre sistematica y zoogeografia de Pentatomidae" type="journal article" year="1962">Pirán, 1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="PIRAN, A. A." box="[1118,1176,305,328]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zool. Lilloana" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="197 - 208" part="26" refId="ref4037" refString="PIRAN, A. A. 1971. La familia Tessaratomidae (Hemiptera-Heteroptera) en la region neotropical. Acta Zool. Lilloana 26: 197 - 208." title="La familia Tessaratomidae (Hemiptera-Heteroptera) en la region neotropical" type="journal article" year="1971">1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
